= People First: The Heart of China's Development

Good morning, everyone.

Today, I'd like to talk about the idea of people first.

In my opinion, "people first" means that people should always be at the center of development. The purpose of a country's development is not only to become richer or stronger, but also to help people live better, safer, and happier lives.

We can see this idea in many parts of daily life in China. For example, schools are improving, so students can have better learning conditions. Medical services are becoming more convenient, so people can get help more easily. In many places, the environment is cleaner, transportation is better, and community services are more complete. There are also more services for children and the elderly. All these changes show that development is meaningful only when it benefits the people.

I think this idea is also important for us as college students. "People first" is not far away from our lives. It can be shown in small things we do every day. In school, it means respecting others, helping classmates, and caring about people around us. In society, it means paying attention to real problems and trying to make life better for others.

As young people, maybe we cannot do something great right now, but we can start with small actions. We can listen to others more carefully, help classmates when they have difficulties, and take part in volunteer work. These actions may seem small, but they really matter.

To me, "people first" is not just a slogan. It is a value that reminds us to care about people, respect people, and serve people. A better society is built not only by economic growth, but also by kindness, fairness, and human care.

In conclusion, "people first" is an important idea in contemporary China, and it should also guide our actions. If we always keep people in mind, we can help build a warmer and better society.
